<br>
As a predominantly evil guild we always had at least a dozen SK's or Necros involved casting DoTs and using pets. The level ranges for these monthly events ran the gambit from the mid 20's all the way up to the mid 50's.<br>
<br>
No one lost experience unless they did something foolish, like ran out of the arena. I think, as the event coordinator and guild leader, I would have known if people, including myself, were losing exp. More to the point, the guild would not have continued the practice for well over a year, happily, gladly, and with great enthusiasm and enjoyment and without complaint, if people, especially in their 40's - 50's were losing XP in the process. It simply didnt happen. Someone would have noticed and said something. Including myself.<br>
<br>
So unless something has changed in the last 6mo or unless you have experienced some sort of isolated bug (which does happen I suppose) I do not see how you could be losing exp. <br>
<br>
Btw, I am looking for the link where Smedly stated clearly there was no exp loss inside an arena... I'll post it when I find it.<br>
<br>
G'day all. <p>"The only future in peace, is War."  - Lothraem L'Velve </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulothraem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothraem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.delharen.com/images/sword.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/9/02 4:57:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2499.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion on dealing with EXP loss in arena battles</span><hr size=1> As promised...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=2126">eq.crgaming.com/viewartic...ticle=2126</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The text of which is as follows...<br>
<br>
___________________________<br>
<br>
Abashi, <br>
<br>
I play a shaman, and I’d love to be able to participate in PvP combat. However, because the shaman has both pets, and DoTs, I can’t /dual someone without the possibility of causing them an experience loss death. Apparently, the system scores a DoT or pet death the same as a fall or drown death, and forces experience loss. Although I think Verant should address this issue, and dedicate the resources needed to fix this bug, you have stated in the past that this is not a priority for Verant. Since this is the case, I was wondering if it would be possible to at leas turn off ALL experience loss in the Arena? There are no MOBs in this zone, and the only way to die is through PvP combat or a fall death. I can’t see how allowing people to fall to their death with no experience loss in one zone would cause any problems, and it would allow people to participate in ‘safe’ PvP combat. So, is there any reason why this can’t be done?<br>
<br>
(Abashi) There's no XP loss for any death encountered while in the PK region of the Arena. Feel free to battle to your hearts content inside there. <br>
<br>
(And later - after many players claimed this was incorrect...)<br>
<br>
Ok, let me clarify then, you *can't* lose experience if you die in the PvP section of the Arena. This is not an accident, *but how it was setup specifically in code to allow battles in this area to take place without that risk*. I did go in and do some tests prior to posting, and *nothing* I was able to do caused experience loss, including:<br>
<br>
1. Death by NPC<br>
2. Death by DOT<br>
3. Death by DD<br>
4. Death by own spell (causes experience loss on ALL servers)<br>
5. Death by bleeding to death<br>
6. Death by falling <br>
<br>
Death by pet still needs to be checked, but it all uses the same code. Perhaps Monday I'll log in and see if someone is willing to have their pet beat me to death there. <br>
<br>
- Gordon<br>
<br>
_______________________________<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope that helps to clarify.<br>
